00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,416
Amazon Location Services Overview

2
00:00:02,875 --> 00:00:18,041
Amazon Location Service is a fully managed
service that developers can use to add location data to applications without sacrificing data security and user privacy. Amazon Location provides maps from multiple sources, built-in tracking, and geofencing capabilities.

3
00:00:19,166 --> 00:00:20,791
Here are some key benefits

4
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:23,000
AWS Integration

5
00:00:23,125 --> 00:00:42,833
Amazon Location Service is fully
integrated with services such as AWS CloudTrail, Amazon CloudWatch, Amazon EventBridge, and AWS Identity and Access Management. Amazon Location streamlines your development workflow with data integration, and it fast tracks apps to production with built-in monitoring, security, and compliance features.

6
00:00:43,375 --> 00:00:44,750
Secure and private

7
00:00:44,916 --> 00:01:06,208
With Amazon Location Service, you retain
control of your organization’s data. Amazon Location anonymizes all queries sent to data providers by removing customer metadata and account information. Additionally, sensitive tracking and geofencing location information, such as facility, asset, and personnel locations, does not leave your AWS account at all.

8
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:08,541
Location functionalities

9
00:01:08,666 --> 00:01:22,166
Using Amazon Location, you can add
location data and functionality to applications, which includes capabilities such as maps, points of interest, geocoding, routing, geofences, and tracking with high-quality data from trusted providers.

10
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:24,375
Here are some key features

11
00:01:24,750 --> 00:01:25,541
Maps

12
00:01:25,750 --> 00:01:42,958
Amazon Location Service Maps helps you
visualize location information and is the foundation of many location-based service capabilities. Amazon Location provides map tiles of different styles sourced from global location data providers. ESRI, GrabMaps, and HERE.

13
00:01:43,583 --> 00:01:44,333
Routing

14
00:01:44,666 --> 00:02:02,791
Amazon Location Service Routes helps you
find routes and estimate travel time based on up-to-date roadway and lyve traffic information. Build features that allow your application to request the travel time, distance, and directions between any two locations. Calculate the time and distance for a matrix of routes to use in route planning.

15
00:02:03,375 --> 00:02:04,458
Geofencing

16
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:24,541
Amazon Location Service Geofences helps
you give your application the ability to detect and act when a device enters or exits a deﬁned geographical boundary, known as a geofence. Automatically send an entry or exit event to Amazon EventBridge when a geofence breach is detected so that you can initiate downstream actions, such as sending a notiﬁcation to a target.

